President Barack Obama announced the appointment of Kimberly Teehee as the Senior Policy Advisor for Native American Affairs. Teehee, a member of the Cherokee Nation, will advise the President on issues impacting Indian Country. President Obama also announced that the White House will hold a Tribal Nations Conference later in the year. Teehee has previously served as a Senior Advisor to Congressman Dale Kildee and as the Director of Native American Outreach for President Clinton's second Inauguration. She has also held various positions with the Cherokee Nation of Oklahoma. President Obama expressed his commitment to strengthening the Nation-to-Nation relationship between the United States and tribal nations and acknowledged the outstanding team of leaders and experts he has chosen to join his Administration in working towards this goal. He also expressed his eagerness to engage with Indian Country on their priorities and announced the upcoming Tribal Nations Conference.